heroes.bio: Superman is one of the last children of Krypton, sent as the dying planet's last hope to Earth, where he grew to become its kind, noble protector. Using his flight, enhanced strength, heat vision, and various other powers, he protects the planet and the universe from powerful threats, all while inspiring hope into others. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

Batman is the superhero protector of Gotham City, a tortured, brooding vigilante dressed as a bat who fights against evil and strikes fear into the hearts of criminals everywhere. His physical prowess, technical ingenuity, and tactical thinking make him an incredibly dangerous opponent. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

Wonder Woman is an Amazon warrior princess and one of the most powerful superheroes in the DC Universe. The daughter of Hippolyta, Wonder Woman of Themyscira was given power by the Gods of Olympus to fight against evil in all its forms. With her Lasso of Truth, magic gauntlets, and an invisible jet she fights crime and spreads her idealistic message of strength and love. She is also a founding member of the Justice League.

Green Lantern is the superhero protector of Coast City and a member of the intergaltic space force known as The Green Lantern Corps. Along with other Green Lanterns, it is his job to patrol the galaxies serving and protecting all life. With his incredible willpower and ability to make solid light constructs Green Lantern is a powerful adversary. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

The Flash is the fastest man alive. With his ability to tap into the speed force The Flash can run at superhuman speeds and travel through time. With this incredible gift and sense of justice he is the protector for those in need in both his home Central City and the rest of the world. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

Aquaman is a superhero and the ruler of the seas. As the king of Atlantis and other undersea territories, he technically controls most of the planet. His abilities include super-strength, durability, super-speed, staying underwater indefinitely, and telepathy, which he uses to communicate with sea-life. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

Green Arrow is a vigilante superhero who fights crime using archery, technology, and martial arts. As a young child, Green Arrow idolized his hero Robin Hood and was said to be a natural archer, frequently practicing with his bow and arrows. As he reached adulthood he donned his own masked archer costume and made it his mission to protect Star City. Later on he became a member of the Justice League.

Martian Manhunter is a superhero from the planet Mars and the last surviving member of his race. His natural abilities include super-strength, super-speed, invulnerability, flight, shape-shifting, intangibility and telepathy. He has been a member of almost every incarnation of the Justice League of America. Although he holds great reverence for his homeworld, he has come to greatly respect his adopted world as well and protects it as his home. He is also a founding member of the Justice League.

cities.name: Coast City
cities.bio: Coast City is a California urban center located less than half an hour from Edwards Air Force Base and twenty minutes from Fort Rock. Many air fields and military bases surround Coast City , which boasts an equally impressive marina and naval station off of its shores. The private aviation company, Ferris Aircraft, once owned by Carl Ferris, has long been tied to and has employed many retired and discharged airmen from Edwards over the years. cities.name: Central City
cities.bio: Central City is a large city located across the Missouri River from Keystone City, Kansas, and with it is known as one of the Gem Cities. Founded in the 19th century, it became an important stop for cattle drives. It began to see tremendous growth after the completion of the Transcontinental Railroad, becoming the first major hub west of Chicago. It is also home to the superhero

cities.name: Amnesty Bay
cities.bio: Amnesty Bay is a small coastal town located in Maine. It is an important location for fishing and trade boats to dock, and  is also a popular tourist site with its beautiful beaches and water. A popular reastuarant, Sam's Seafood Reasturant, is located off the boardwalk and is sought out by visitors. It is also home to the superhero

cities.name: Star City
cities.bio: Star City, also known in earlier times as Fort Plymouth and Starling City, is a bustling tech capital in northern California. Founded in the year 1797, Star City grew into a prosperous trading community luring prospectors all the way from Canada to ply their trades. Since then it has contiuned to grow into a thriving city with giant corporate headquarters such as Queen Industries. It is also home to the vigilante known as the

cities.name: The Watchtower
cities.bio: The Justice League Watchtower is the headquarters of the Justice League of America. The Watchtower was constructed of promethium and used highly advanced Martian, Thanagarian, Kryptonian and Terran technology. The arrival of Orion and Big Barda added the technology of New Genesis and Apokolips to the systems within.
